```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return Symbol(lowercase(strip(col, whitespace), replace(col, '-' => '_')))
end
```

This function takes an `AbstractString` as input and returns a `Symbol` with the cleaned column name. It first lowers the case of the string using `lowercase()`, strips leading and trailing whitespaces using `strip(..., whitespace)`, and then replaces any spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace(..., '-' => '_')`. Finally, it converts the result back to a `Symbol`.
